            <step2>
                <para count="1">Choose the correct spacer washer according to the dial indicator reading in step 12.
                    Refer to the
                    <hotlnk xrefid="t1303304">Spacer Washer Measurement Chart above</hotlnk>
                    to choose the correct spacer washer.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the countershaft end play checking tool.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the blue spacer washer that was used to check the end play.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install the correct spacer washer in the bore on top of the cup. Make sure the tab of
                    the washer is aligned with the slot in the case
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1393317">(Figure 376)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install the cover for auxiliary countershaft.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install the bolts and washers that fasten the cover to the auxiliary case.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Alternately and evenly tighten the bolts until the countershaft cover touches the
                    surface of the auxiliary cover DO NOT TIGHTEN MORE THAN 47 NM (35 FT-LBS.).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolts, washers and countershaft cover.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Again check the end play for the auxiliary countershaft. Refer to steps 2 through 9.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1393317" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/g1393317.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 376. Install Spacer Washer</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a sealant dispenser and Loctite RTV Sealant or equivalent to put a 3 mm (1/8 inch) new
                sealant pattern for the cover of the auxiliary countershaft in the pattern shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1393318">Figure 377</hotlnk>. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s13033_11.xml" xrefid="x1303304">INSTALLING THE SEALANT</hotlnk>
                section.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1393318" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/g1393318.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 377. Sealant Pattern</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the cover for the auxiliary countershaft on the auxiliary case. Install the bolts
                and washers. Tighten the bolts to 34 to 47 Nm (25 to 35 ft-lbs.)
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1393319">(Figure 378).</hotlnk>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1393319" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/g1393319.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 378. Tighten Bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Different end play measurements of each countershaft are a normal condition.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repeat steps 2 through 12 and check the end play of the other auxiliary countershaft.
                Correct end play is 0.051 to 0.152 mm (.002 to .006 inch).
            </para>
        </step1>
